This paper is about the simulation of neural networks, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE). The paper also mentions the use of distributed computing and the Human Brain Project, which suggests a focus on large-scale systems and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The study involves measuring the impact of different connectivity models on the scaling behavior and memory occupation of the network, which could be considered a machine learning problem (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of hardware and MPI processes, indicating a focus on systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the study is conducted in the context of the CORTICONIC FET project, which is related to computational cognitive neuroscience (cs.CC).
